p.01703376c4a81c0e9d91: Transform a Cloud Object to JSON
p.01703376c4a81c0e9d92:
Transform an instance of a Cloud Object or list of instances to JSON. The properties of the related business model are used as properties of the json. ## Example CloudObjectToJSON(`GPS Coordinate` object) ->
"Latitude":15, "Longitude": 25," name": "GPS Coordinate" }

CloudObjectToJSON(`List of GPS Coordinate` objects) ->
[ { "Latitude":15, "Longitude": 25, "name": "GPS Coordinate"},
{ "Latitude": 13, "Longitude": 22, " name" : "GPS Coordinate" } ]
Instance of Cloud Object or List

If true, only consider the properties of cloud objects.

Otherwise, includes the relations and serialize the related cloudobjects recursively.
Warning: only consider the cloudobjects already loaded in the local database.
JSON object or array of objects
Triggered if provided source is not a correct Cloud Object of List of Cloud Objects
